review 1:
What an idyllic place. Bali as I like it. Located in one of the most beautiful villages I have ever been in Bali.
The cooking class and Jamu making were amazing. The walk along the ricefields shows a Bali as it used to be.
Worth to visit if you love Bali as I do.
review 2: This was a very special trip into the origin nature of Bali to see and experience the overwhelming abundance, like fruits, spices and herbs. The guide told us what you can find edible along the way and the cooking class added the healthy effect of herbs and spices in a "power morning shot" like Beras Kencur and Jamu Kunyit Jahre Asam! Now I enjoy the delicious balinese food with the healthy, tasty ingredients even more. The cook and his friendly team made my day and after all, added a hot shower in the nearby hot spring make me feel 20 years younger ;-)
